Industrial Carpenter National Center for Construction Education and Research An industrial carpenter erects concrete forms, plumb,
level, and grade; places embeds; rigs large formwork;
has a working knowledge of earthworks and
reinforcement; may operate equipment needed to place
concrete; reads and interprets construction drawings;
operates measuring instruments. Core

